From 8222ed80c942e674db859f51ecde9330f6cfef11 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Arnaud Juracek <arnaud.juracek@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 20:36:34 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 07/17] Serialize artwork title, fix broken /testimonies and
 /testimony routes

- artworks.rs: read title_en/fr/nl and populate ResultArtwork.title
  (InternationalizedString, None when all three are empty), matching
  the DB migration that added artworks.title_fr/nl/en.
- testimonies.rs/main.rs: the testimonies table has a `city` column,
  not `location_id` as the code assumed -- every /testimonies and
  POST /testimony call was failing with "no such column: location_id".
  Renamed the Rust-side field/param to `city` to match the actual
  schema instead of renaming the DB. New-testimony route param renamed
  from `l` to `c` for consistency with the `city` field name.
- pp1_collection.db: refreshed from the database repo (title_* columns
  added by migrate_v4.py, city untouched).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
